  \lim_{x \to \infty} \frac {xe^{x/2}}{1+e^x}\quad?
x\rightarrow+\infty
0\cdot 1=0
 \frac{xe^{x/2}}{1+e^x}=\frac{x}{e^{x/2}}\frac{1}{1+e^{-x}}. 
e^{x/2}
\lim_{x\to\infty} {xe^{x/2}\over 1 + e^x} = \lim_{x\to\infty}{e^{x/2} + (1/2)xe^{x/2}\over e^x}. 
  \lim_{x \to \infty}\; \frac {x\,e^{x/2}}{1+e^x}\;=\; \lim _{x\to \infty}\;\left[\left(\frac{x}{e^{x/2}}\right)\left(\frac{1}{1+e^{-x}}\right)\right]\; = \; (0)\cdot(1) = 0
 
